-- Colombia Stocks: Petrominerales, Pacific Rubiales, Ecopetrol
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-07-13T22:03:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-13/colombia-stocks-pacific-rubiales-canacol-ecopetrol-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 1.2 percent to 13,664.64 while the
Colcap Index increased 0.8 percent to 1,657.84.  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMGC)  , a Calgary-based  oil company 
that operates in the Andean region, fell 1.6 percent to 17,900
pesos, a record low closing level. Former Colombian President
 Alvaro Uribe  posted to his 1.3 million  Twitter  followers that
Petrominerales would halt some explorations for security
reasons.  Petrominerales Ltd. said road blockades have halted oil
production at two wells in Colombia since April. The company
also temporarily suspended exploration in part of eastern
Colombia after separate protests in April there, according to a
statement distributed today by e-mail.  Other oil producers gained as crude rose for a third day in
New York.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , which operates the
country’s largest oil field, jumped 3.1 percent to 40,740 pesos.
 Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company, rose
0.8 percent to 4,970 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Jenkins in  New York  at 
